<div id="sendoutlook">
  <% if @partial_is_popup %>
  <a href="#" onclick="close_csv3()">x Close Window</a>
  <% end %>

  <center>
    <p><b>To upload an Outlook style CSV file of contacts from Hotmail</b></p>
    <br />
    <p>To export a CSV or tab-delimited text file from Hotmail:</p>
    <br />

    <p>  1. In Hotmail: Select Contacts from the lower left hand portion of the screen. </p>
    <p>  2. Go to the "Manage" tab at the top of the screen.</p>
    <p>  3. Select "Export"</p>
    <p>  4. Click Save when prompted what to do with the file download.</p>
    <p>  5. Choose the location where you want to save the Hotmail csv copy of your contacts & save.</p>
    <br />
    <p>To upload your file to TheWeddingRegistry, simply hit "Browse" below and select the contact file you've just created.</p>
    <br />
    <br />
    <%= form_tag({:controller => :contact_lists,:action => :import_from_yahoo_post}, :multipart => true) do %>
    <div id="csv_import" style="display: inline;">
      <p>Yahoo CSV file: <input name="csv" type="file"></p>
      <br />
      <%= submit_tag "Browse",class: "btn btn-success" %>
    </div>
    <% end %>
  </center>
</div>
